{% schema %}
  {
    
    "name": "Section 2",
    "tag": "section",
    "class": "gps-599867440930751340 gps gpsil",
    "settings": [{"type":"paragraph","content":"Section design by GemPages. [Click here to start design](https://admin.shopify.com/store/w7f2j0-0h/apps/gempages-cro/app/shopify/edit?pageType=GP_STATIC&editorId=599853785602327189&sectionId=599867440930751340)"},{"type":"select","label":"Section Preload","id":"section_preload","options":[{"label":"On","value":"true"},{"label":"Off","value":"false"},{"label":"Off Lazy Script","value":"off_lazy_script"}],"default":"false"},{"type":"text","label":"Checksum","id":"checksum"},{"type":"html","id":"ggI2OyToJXX_text","label":"ggI2OyToJXX_text","default":"1. You’re Polishing \"Dead Wood\" Instead of Feeding the Root"},{"type":"html","id":"ggE6YJoWgko_text","label":"ggE6YJoWgko_text","default":"<p>Most shampoos are designed to make the hair you already have look shiny. But the hair strand on your head is technically dead tissue. If you want real change, you have to go to the \"factory\" the scalp. Think of your <strong>crown</strong> like a garden. If the soil is dry and packed hard, even the best seeds won't grow. <strong>Radiant Root </strong>doesn't just coat the hair; it \"tills the soil\" so your follicles can finally breathe again.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggCSMdB5uDP_text","label":"ggCSMdB5uDP_text","default":"2. The \"Clogged Pore\" Paradox (Why the Serums Stay on Top)"},{"type":"html","id":"ggkqI3koa6W_text","label":"ggkqI3koa6W_text","default":"<p>You wouldn't expect clear skin if you never washed your pores, right? Yet, for years, you’ve likely used \"thickening\" products loaded with heavy silicones. These create a microscopic \"crust\" that suffocates the follicle. This is why your expensive serums never work they literally can’t get through. By switching to a scalp focused cleanser, you remove this 3-year barrier, allowing nutrients to finally reach the bulb.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg0Ec4UHS_s_text","label":"gg0Ec4UHS_s_text","default":"3. The Rosemary \"Circulation Spark\""},{"type":"html","id":"ggh1vTawJsJ_text","label":"ggh1vTawJsJ_text","default":"<p>There’s a reason you see so many women talking about Rosemary in our videos. According to <strong>Wilhelm Wundt’s</strong> principles of physiological psychology, our bodies need a sensory \"spark\" to trigger a response. When you feel that slight, fresh tingle on your scalp, it’s not just a sensation it’s micro-circulation. This blood flow is the \"delivery truck\" for the nutrients your hair needs to go from \"peach fuzz\" to actual strands.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggq0plmZwvW_text","label":"ggq0plmZwvW_text","default":"4. Stopping the \"Drain Drama\" (The Keratin Scaffold)"},{"type":"html","id":"ggU1wLgJUrS_text","label":"ggU1wLgJUrS_text","default":"<p>The most heartbreaking part of hair loss is seeing clumps in the shower drain. This is often \"mechanical shedding\" caused by a weak anchor. Our <strong>Keratin Mechanism</strong> acts as a structural scaffold, reinforcing the point where the hair meets the scalp. This gives you the immediate \"Sensory Proof\" <strong>Claude Hopkins</strong> insisted was vital: you’ll notice less hair in your brush and more \"baby hairs\" filling in your hairline within weeks.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg8n6hnXUGx_text","label":"gg8n6hnXUGx_text","default":"5. The \"Shampoo Switch\" (The Law of Least Effort)"},{"type":"html","id":"ggBrq_0CuGA_text","label":"ggBrq_0CuGA_text","default":"<p><strong>David Ogilvy</strong> knew that busy women don't want a 7-step medical chore. You’ve been dealing with this for 3 years you don’t need more work. The \"Scalp-First\" routine works because it’s a simple swap. You’re already washing your hair; Radiant Root just ensures that every wash is actually a \"follicle revival\" treatment. It’s the easiest way to reclaim your confidence without changing your morning.</p>"}],
    "blocks": [{"type": "@app"}],
    "locales": {}
